      "text": "Last edit almost 3 years ago by svayambhu108\n130\nNeeds Review\n130\nC-214 the fusion of the Gnostic idea of heim armene + the breaking of heimarmene (which implies a transtemporal deity. man + God against world, etc) with the Orthodox Xtian view of man in bondage to Satan by reason of sin (in fact original sin) creates an ultra‐ system, for it abolishes the issue of God the creator + God as transmundane in contradistinction to a blind demi‐ urge creator, + abolishes the issue of Gnosis versus just",
      "matched_alias": "Pauline",
      "term_id": "TERM_pauline",
      "term_name": "Pauline",
      "term_slug": "pauline"
    },
    {
      "text": "Last edit almost 3 years ago by svayambhu108\n\n131\nG-215 so that he has nothing (ordinarily) to contrast it to. (This relates to my arch -theme of occlusion: that man does not see - is not allowed to see - his real condition + the real nature of world). the theme of acosmism comes in this way: Just as the Gnostics say \"astrology is right until Baptism\" I say \"world is real -binding + absolute - until the \"transaction of justification - in which through the ransom man is freed of the binding power",
      "matched_alias": "Pauline",
      "term_id": "TERM_pauline",
